\vec u = (-2,3) \\ \vec v = (2,4)
2\vec u-\frac12\vec v = (-5,4)
\begin{aligned} \vec{u} &= (-2,3)\\ \vec{v} &= (2,4) \end{aligned}
c(a,b) = (ca,cb)
\begin{aligned} 2\vec{u} - \dfrac{1}{2}\vec{v} &= 2(-2,3) - \dfrac{1}{2}(2,4) & \text{[Given]}\\ &= (2 \cdot -2, 2 \cdot 3) - \left(\frac{1}{2} \cdot 2, \frac{1}{2} \cdot 4 \right) & \text{[$c(a,b) = (ca,cb)$]}\\ &= (-4,6) - (1, 2)\\ &= (-4 - 1, 6 - 2) & \text{[Combine both vectors coordinate-wise.]}\\ &= (-5, 4) \end{aligned}
